.TH URL_TO_STR 3 "13 June 2024"
.SH NAME
url_to_str \- gets the URL as a string from url_t*
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.ft B
#include <ncsnet/url.h>
void    url_to_str(url_t *url, char *buf, size_t buflen);
.ft
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR url_to_str ()
assembles the fields of the
.B url_t*
object into a string representation of the URL address, which it writes to the
.B buf
buffer with size
.BR buflen .
.PP
.B NOTE:
to get the exact size for the buffer, you can use
.BR url_len ().
